    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-12T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-12T05:00:00-05:00" n="574"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d574">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12566: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-12T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 12 [<hi rend="italic">16?</hi>], 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 16—10:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>913. Department’s 394, December 16 [<hi rend="italic">14</hi>] 4 [<hi
                        rend="italic">6</hi>] p.m. I have instructed Peck at Nanking to hand to the
                    Foreign Office an <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> acknowledging receipt of
                    the Foreign Office note of November 25th and stating the position of the
                    American Government in the same terms as stated in the <hi rend="italic"
                        >aide-mémoire</hi> handed by me to the Foreign Office on May 19, 1930 which
                    [was reported?] in the Legation’s telegram No. 355, May 21, 4 p.m., 1930.<note
                        n="70" xml:id="d574fn70">
                        <ref target="frus1930v02#pg_121">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1930, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 121</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
